AB  - This paper attempts to generalise the Young-Miyagiwa results for an economy with a free trade zone and Harris-Todaro unemployment by incorporating intersectoral mobility of domestic capital and an upward sloping supply function of foreign capital. Our analysis reveals, that under reasonable assumptions, creating a free trade zone may lead to a loss in national welfare. Further, there may arise a conflict between the twin objectives of increasing employment and increasing national welfare.
